<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-04T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–454: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BOHLENCEC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bohlen</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-04T20:00:00+03:00">September
                                    4, 1954—8 p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>324. Thai Minister here says he has received instructions from his
                            government to ask for Soviet support of <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> Presidential candidacy of <persName corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1">Prince Wan</persName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BOHLENCEC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bohlen</hi>
                                </persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>